headline: 3 Reasons to Sell DGX and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Quest’s 12.9% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 7.7%, and its stock price has climbed to $173.97 per share. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
